HEADWORD: Smew
<hw>Smew</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Perhaps for
<ets>ice-mew</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>small
European merganser (<spn>Mergus albellus</spn>) which has a white crest;
-- called also <altname>smee</altname>, <altname>smee duck</altname>,
<altname>white merganser</altname>, and <altname>white
nun</altname>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The hooded merganser.</def>
<mark>[Local, U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

